    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="485"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/92.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister to Haiti</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In regard to your December 2,<note n="4" xml:id="d485fn4">Should be December 22;
                        see <ref target="frus1911#pg_166">For. Rel. 1911, p. 166</ref>.</note>
                    January 8, and No. 993 of December 23<note n="2" xml:id="d485fn2">see <ref
                            target="frus1911#pg_166">For. Rel., 1911, p. 166</ref>.</note>, the
                    Department is gratified to know that the Haitian Government has taken vigorous
                    measures against the Dominican revolutionists, <pb facs="0457" n="341"
                        xml:id="pg_341"/> and that it is willing to broaden the powers of the
                    boundary plenipotentiary. Similar action is being urged at Santo Domingo by our
                    Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
